    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes a dance performed by Southeastern Native North American communities during the Green Corn Ceremony, including the Cherokees, Creeks, and Seminoles. The dance was performed frequently up until the late 19th century, with revivals occurring in the contemporary period.</Note_Text>
